- madoule is a file containing python statements and definantions
- file name is the name of the module witj suffix.py
- each module has its own private namespace 
- modules can import other modules
	e.g -from math import pi
- if module is followed by as then we have renamd the module
	e.g from math import pi as pie
	- then we would use pie instea of pi

=> sys.argv
	- list of commandline arguments passed in a python script
	- argv[0] is the script name


